race.comment: OVERDRIVE (3) is on resumption today on the back of a very nice trial at this track where she won easily under a strong hold. She has only won 1/10, but she's shown good ability throughout her career and looks ready to capitalise on that now. Finds a suitable race on resumption and can land the knockout blow. SAVAGE DANCER (8) was very good on debut before going straight to the paddock. That form worked out well and her latest trial coming into this was very impressive. Likely to get back from the draw but can storm home over the top to remain unbeaten. SESH (4) just missed two back before rising to 1100m last start and finishing 2L off the winner. Back to 1000m today looks a good move and he maps well from the barrier. Can bounce back to his best and be in the finish. GALWAY SHAWL (6) won well on debut and is not to be discounted heading into this event. SPICY THANG (10) can feature in the finish if she brings her best.
